the fruitiest shirt in my closet,

16:15.976 --> 16:17.978
and he's gonna be here in 20 minutes.

16:19.271 --> 16:23.317
- Okay, uh, well... I think I can help.

16:23.317 --> 16:24.651
- How can you help?

16:25.485 --> 16:28.113
- [gently] Okay, Rahim,
here's what we're gonna do.

16:28.113 --> 16:32.159
First, you need to put the pencil down,
and then come with me.

16:32.159 --> 16:33.994
- God, is that really what I sounded like?

16:34.536 --> 16:35.996
How did you not punch me in the face?

16:35.996 --> 16:37.998
- It was hard.
Come on.

16:41.126 --> 16:43.128
♪

16:48.050 --> 16:50.219
- Hey. How's it goin'? You okay?

16:50.677 --> 16:52.429
- It's not an STI.

16:52.429 --> 16:56.808
It's poison ivy
which I probably got from

16:56.808 --> 16:58.769
hooking up with Nick in his backyard.

16:58.769 --> 17:00.729
- Okay! That's great.

17:00.729 --> 17:03.774
Hey, put some cream on the ween
and get back out there.

17:03.774 --> 17:04.983
- I guess it's just--

17:05.776 --> 17:08.403
If I was still with Benji,
none of this would've happened.

17:08.904 --> 17:12.908
And even if it did, like, we would've
gone through it together, you know?

17:14.993 --> 17:15.994
- L--
[phone buzzes]

17:16.870 --> 17:18.497
- Go.
- Yeah, just one sec.

17:19.957 --> 17:21.375
Hey, babe. What's up?

17:21.375 --> 17:22.918
- My parents found out about us.

17:22.918 --> 17:25.128
My dad's furious.
He wouldn't even let me explain.

17:25.128 --> 17:28.715
- No. Hey, hey, hey. It's okay.
We're, we're in this together, all right?

17:28.715 --> 17:29.675
- You don't get it.

17:29.675 --> 17:31.844
Now he's gonna try to, like,
forbid us from being together,

17:31.844 --> 17:33.470
but... no.

17:33.470 --> 17:35.639
I refuse to let him stop me
from seeing the guy I love.

17:35.639 --> 17:40.102
- Ah, wait... Ah, you, uh, y-y--
Ya love me?

17:42.271 --> 17:45.482
- Oh, I... I didn't mean--
That just slipped out.

17:45.482 --> 17:48.110
- No, no. Hey, Pilar, I, I...

17:49.236 --> 17:50.237
I love you, too.

17:51.280 --> 17:53.490
Uh, hey, uh, let's, um--

17:54.157 --> 17:55.909
Just wait 'til I get home.

17:55.909 --> 17:59.288
'Kay? We'll... figure this out together.
We'll talk to your parents.

17:59.288 --> 18:02.833
'Kay?
- Okay.

18:07.087 --> 18:08.922
- So, she loves me.
[Victor chuckles]

18:09.798 --> 18:11.425
Kinda the best day ever.

18:13.302 --> 18:15.304
- I'm happy for you guys.
- Thanks, man.

18:25.731 --> 18:26.732
- Hey.

18:28.650 --> 18:33.447
Uhh, it's weird being in a fight
when we live in the same house.

18:33.447 --> 18:35.574
- Normally, I would just
dramatically hang up on you

18:35.574 --> 18:37.993
and not have to see you later
eating my yogurt.

18:39.912 --> 18:45.000
- I'm, I'm sorry for, uh, pressuring you
to talk to your mom about Lucy.

18:45.000 --> 18:46.793
That is 100% your decision,

18:46.793 --> 18:48.420
and you should only
do it when you're ready.

18:50.380 --> 18:54.510
- Thank you.
- And I'm always on your side.

18:56.094 --> 18:59.097
I just got swept up in our day

18:59.681 --> 19:02.476
'cause she was fun and nice,

19:02.476 --> 19:07.481
and... it felt good to have
a mom take interest in my life.

19:08.023 --> 19:09.024
- I know.

19:10.025 --> 19:12.861
I'm not even mad at you.
I'm mad at her.

19:13.612 --> 19:18.492
It would make my life so much easier
if I could just tell her about Lucy,

19:18.492 --> 19:21.495
but... I can't.

19:23.121 --> 19:26.542
The more I like something,
the more she criticizes it.

19:27.751 --> 19:31.296
In the seventh grade,
I saved up all of my birthday money

19:31.296 --> 19:34.633
to buy this super cute
plaid jacket from Forever 21.

19:34.633 --> 19:37.344
- Hm, I remember that jacket.
You wore it everywhere.

19:37.344 --> 19:40.264
- And then my mom told me
that I looked like a bagpipe,

19:40.264 --> 19:41.515
and I never wore it again.

19:43.350 --> 19:45.394
She poisons everything.

19:45.394 --> 19:49.982
- Well, maybe it's time you tell your mom
how these criticisms make you feel.

19:50.899 --> 19:52.442
- Yeah, maybe.

19:53.569 --> 19:55.612
There's an "L" here on the lid.
- I--

19:55.612 --> 19:59.032
- "L" for Lake. I'm just gonna take this.
- Okay.

20:01.785 --> 20:04.371
- You'd be surprised what you
can find in the lost and found.

20:05.122 --> 20:07.249
- Anything'll do. I'm not picky.

20:07.249 --> 20:09.251
- All right... here you go.

20:09.251 --> 20:11.837
- No, never.
I'd rather watch baseball.

20:15.048 --> 20:16.884
- Hey, listen.

20:16.884 --> 20:20.888
Sorry for being a jerk...
about the tutoring.

20:21.847 --> 20:24.683
Sometimes when I'm overwhelmed, I can be--

20:25.934 --> 20:27.144
I can be kind of an asshole.

20:27.728 --> 20:28.896
- Why are you overwhelmed?

20:28.896 --> 20:31.523
- I just feel like
I'm disappointing everybody.

20:33.859 --> 20:36.236
I mean, my parents
don't even know about my grades.

20:36.236 --> 20:39.865
They already see me
as this giant failure, my drinking.

20:40.741 --> 20:42.618
I don't know how to tell 'em
I'm failing one more thing.

20:43.535 --> 20:45.954
- Guess we can't say we don't
know anything about each other.

20:46.663 --> 20:50.292
- Yeah, both our family situations suck.
- Yeah.

20:50.918 --> 20:53.921
Ah, it's so ugly.
- Oh, c'mon.

20:53.921 --> 20:55.506
You're tryna look straight. It's perfect.

20:55.506 --> 20:57.132
- [sighs] Fine.

21:02.513 --> 21:05.933
- Mm... first Victor and now me.

21:06.683 --> 21:09.228
Mm, you gotta stop
tryin' to seduce people.

21:09.228 --> 21:10.229
- Shut up.

21:14.066 --> 21:16.109
- Mi amor, what're you doin'?

21:16.109 --> 21:20.197
- I am gonna take our daughter's door...
off the hinges.

21:22.241 --> 21:25.327
- Okay, probably shouldn't be saying this
while you're holding a sharp object,

21:25.327 --> 21:29.665
but I've been thinking
and, um, Pilar has a point.

21:29.665 --> 21:30.707
- Excuse me?

21:30.707 --> 21:34.670
- When it comes to dating,
you do tend to fly off the handle,

21:34.670 --> 21:38.674
and I know that it comes
from a good place, but it's, it's a lot.

21:38.674 --> 21:39.842
- Well, I'm her father.

21:39.842 --> 21:42.845
It's my job to protect her.
She's just a little girl.

21:43.887 --> 21:48.016
- Okay, actually... that's the point.

21:48.016 --> 21:50.435
She isn't a little girl.

21:52.604 --> 21:56.024
Pilar is growing up,
and whether you like it or not,

21:56.024 --> 21:58.026
she's gonna have boyfriends.

21:58.902 --> 22:03.156
We should be thankful that it's Felix.
He's, he's sweet. He's smart.

22:03.782 --> 22:07.661
He's not gonna... push her
into something that she's not ready for.

22:09.079 --> 22:12.708
- He's all right.
- Come on, you like Felix.

22:14.501 --> 22:15.711
- Uhh.

22:18.046 --> 22:19.756
Pilar, come on out!

22:19.756 --> 22:21.383
[door opens]

22:30.559 --> 22:34.563
It's been brought to my attention
that I could've handled this differently.

22:38.358 --> 22:40.944
- Felix wanted to tell
you guys a million times.

22:40.944 --> 22:42.321
I made him keep it a secret

22:42.321 --> 22:45.699
because... I didn't want
you to scare him off.

22:46.783 --> 22:49.786
But it's real. We love each other.

22:51.330 --> 22:53.040
- You love each other?

22:53.040 --> 22:56.835
Ay... what do you say?

23:00.297 --> 23:03.133
- We're okay. But no more secrets.

23:03.634 --> 23:06.220
- No more secrets. I promise.

23:07.179 --> 23:08.597
[knocks on door]

23:10.140 --> 23:11.433
- [whispers] That was great.

23:19.733 --> 23:20.984
- Guys, this is my fault.

23:22.069 --> 23:25.739
Okay? And I, I, I wanna let you know,
I have grounded myself.

23:25.739 --> 23:28.742
And so, any chore you need me
to pick up, nothing's too gross.

23:28.742 --> 23:31.328
- Felix, shut up. They're on board.

23:33.789 --> 23:34.790
- Really?!

23:35.582 --> 23:40.170
Aw, guys, bring it in!
Mama Salazar, Papa!

23:40.170 --> 23:42.548
Oh!
[Isabel chuckles]

23:42.548 --> 23:46.969
Papa!
- Ah, okay. I'm already regretting this.

23:50.764 --> 23:52.683
♪

23:52.683 --> 23:54.268
[phone dings]

24:08.490 --> 24:10.951
[ringback tone]

24:10.951 --> 24:12.578
NICK [voicemail]:
Hey, it's Nick. Leave a message.

24:12.578 --> 24:16.999
[beeps]
- Uh, hey, Nick. It's Victor, um.

24:18.083 --> 24:20.252
I just thought it would be better
to call rather than text,

24:20.252 --> 24:21.712
but you're not answering,

24:21.712 --> 24:25.424
so I guess I'm gonna
do this over voicemail.

24:26.091 --> 24:27.384
Um...

24:28.969 --> 24:32.389
I want... something more
than "you up" texts.

24:33.432 --> 24:38.437
I want... someone who answers my calls.

24:39.605 --> 24:42.691
And I, I know you've been
super clear about keeping this casual,

24:42.691 --> 24:47.696
which is totally cool... for you.
It's just, um...

24:49.823 --> 24:51.325
it's not really working for me.

24:52.117 --> 24:52.951
[hangs up]

24:57.289 --> 25:00.584
- Oh, Lake, honey, don't slouch.

25:00.584 --> 25:03.128
You're gonna wind up with a turtle body.

25:06.298 --> 25:09.051
- Mom, why do you criticize
everything about me?

25:11.178 --> 25:13.680
- What? Where is this coming from?

25:13.680 --> 25:17.267
- My weight, my clothes,
the way that I sit in this chair.

25:17.267 --> 25:20.479
This morning you corrected
my pronunciation of the word "croissant."

25:20.479 --> 25:22.814
Wait, is that right? Cross-ant? Cwah-san?

25:22.814 --> 25:24.274
I mean, now I don't
even know how to say it.

25:24.274 --> 25:28.737
The point is, you're never happy...
no matter what I do.

25:31.823 --> 25:36.703
- I am so sorry. I had no idea.

25:38.247 --> 25:41.542
So, you know I'm a public persona.
- Yeah, I heard that somewhere.

25:41.542 --> 25:43.293
- Just let me finish.

25:43.293 --> 25:45.295
So, sometimes after the 5:00 news,

25:45.295 --> 25:48.215
I like to go online
and see what the fans have to say.

25:48.215 --> 25:52.845
And... nine times out of 10,
it is not about the story.

25:52.845 --> 25:58.475
It's about my blazer,
or my hair, or my voice,

25:58.475 --> 26:02.062
and I just thought maybe I could help
you present your best self to the world,

26:02.062 --> 26:04.273
and you could avoid that kind of bullying.

26:06.984 --> 26:10.028
But what I hear you saying
is I'm the bully.

26:14.867 --> 26:15.909
Lake,

26:17.995 --> 26:20.205
I think you are perfection.

26:20.205 --> 26:24.585
You're smart and beautiful,
and any boy would be so lucky to have you.

26:28.463 --> 26:30.299
- Actually, Mom, um...

26:31.508 --> 26:33.010
you know my friend, Lucy?

26:35.179 --> 26:37.014
She's not just my friend.

26:39.057 --> 26:40.225
We're together.

26:40.976 --> 26:44.605
- Oh... okay, um.

26:45.731 --> 26:49.526
Well, what does this mean exactly?
Are you bi?

26:50.152 --> 26:51.945
- I actually don't know yet.

26:53.697 --> 26:54.948
Are you okay?

26:54.948 --> 26:56.575
- Of course, I'm okay.

26:58.410 --> 27:01.288
Oh, wait!
This is actually so exciting

27:01.288 --> 27:03.540
because this is perfect
for your college essays.

27:03.540 --> 27:05.501
Finally, something that
makes you interesting.

27:05.501 --> 27:07.127
- Okay, Mom, you're doing it again.
- Okay, yes.

27:07.127 --> 27:08.879
It's gonna take me a minute to unlearn.

27:11.173 --> 27:14.176
♪ Never Going Home
by Hazel English playing ♪

27:20.140 --> 27:22.768
- How'd it go?
- See for yourself.

27:23.602 --> 27:27.314
- Yaas, Gaga,
boots the house down, A minus!

27:27.314 --> 27:30.400
- I don't know what that means,
but, uh, thank you.

27:32.444 --> 27:34.279
- Careful, your hair.
- Mm-hm.

